  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Tomorrow is a New Day: Towards Social Justice and Peace in eSwatini.</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project seeks to improve access to social justice and peace for the women, men and children of eSwatini. In order to achieve this the project takes a three-pronged approach: united, multi-level evidence-based advocacy by Churches; mobilised and strengthened communities engaging their leadership; and a more informed and equipped leadership able to respond to these concerns. The project seeks to address structural and institutional bottlenecks in justice delivery and improve effective justice delivery through better interaction between traditional and formal justice systems and increased observation of rights. CCJP eSwatini is well positioned through its networks to engage at these three levels and the project will support the further development of capacity across the network through support to animators, parish level committees and priests as well as the secretariat itself. Participatory spaces and approaches will be promoted. The Project is premised on the following Theory of Change. 
If Churches speak with a united voice on issues of justice and peace, people will hear their messages and authorities will respond to identified issues; And if communities are empowered through knowledge of their rights and supported to engage with authorities and agree action; And if local formal and traditional leaders have better knowledge of the legal framework, peoples&#x2019; rights and their responsibilities, as well as increased engagement with their constituencies, they will exercise their functions better; Then men, women and children in eSwatini will have improved access to social justice and peace.</narrative>
  </description>
